SIMPLE MYSQL ENCRIPTER/DECRPTER
This Store procedure can Encript and Decript all fealds of any table;
this store procedure allows  to Encript and Decript one of this Format;
AES_DECRYPT()	Decrypt using AES
AES_ENCRYPT()	Encrypt using AES
COMPRESS()	Return result as a binary string
DECODE()	Decode a string encrypted using ENCODE()
DES_DECRYPT()	Decrypt a string
DES_ENCRYPT()	Encrypt a string
ENCODE()	Encode a string
ENCRYPT()	Encrypt a string
MD5()	Calculate MD5 checksum

HOW TO USE:

1) make a store procedure and copy and past my sql;
2) in your dbms :

	call [DATABASE].Cripter(
							'md5'  [one of supported format ],
							[TABLE],
							[SOME QUERY CONDICTION]  example id=1
							);
this return a table with all fealds Decripted/Encripted